			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes, magicians are summoners but some of the people are forgetting you do need to <span style="font-weight: bold">CONTROL</span> what ever you have summoned. 
<br />

<br />
Like someone already had mentioned previously, the blades that you have summon won’t just automatically go and attack its target.  You must have will to control them.  It’s not like when you summon the blades, the blades talk to themselves saying, “hey look guys, master is targeting that mob, lets go kick his arse”, is it?
<br />

<br />
In any event, either by magical contraption or thru the will of Magician, summoned items or elementals are controlled.  Magicians are not all just about summoning stuff.
<br />

<br />
In PoP, is it that wrong that Magicians get to take some utility toward the Elemental mobs?  I believe we are all trained from the beginning of the EQ, summoned mobs are just being someone’s pet.  Not realizing that it’s all about Elemental mobs.  When you take out someone’s pet factor from the mobs that are tagged as summoned, then you begin to realize it’s all about the Elemental Creatures, nothing else other than Elemental Creature.
<br />

<br />
Even if all the elemental utilities that will be or decided to be taken away from the Magician, I wonder what we’ll be getting to benefit us.  Yes… I know some of the people in the board are working hard with the SoE.  But most of the Class balance are already in effect. Close enough at least.
<br />

<br />
But… boys and gals you must get some facts thru your thick skulls that… 
<br />
No… we won’t get far better pet than the Beasty & Necro, probably will be close. 
<br />
No… we won’t get anything that’s been suggested in the board, at least most of them. 
<br />
No… they won’t do or does anything that will make the class balance out of whack nor do anything that will be time consuming… that sure will prompt other classes to be upset!  Why?  Because why in the hell the SoE spend that much of time addressing magicians and not our class? 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I hope we get something good for the trade but... I will thank somebody if it does</span>
<br />

<br />
Anything that involves other than Elemental utility upgrades or advantages, other classes will be up and arms with those advantages that magicians will get.
<br />

<br />
Nobody care what kind of utility we get toward the elemental except… <span style="font-weight: bold">The Magicians apparently</span>.  I have not heard any enchanters complaining about what kind of utilities we have toward the elementals.  They are not complaining that we are stepping on their toes.
<br />

<br />
Just the Magicians are feeling that way… /sigh. 
<br />

<br />
So, don’t be surprised when shit does not fly… It’s all given that class balance is in effect.  Except toward elemental… no one will complaint what kind of advantage the Magicians get toward the elementals, just only the Magicians will complaint.
<br />

<br />
Utility toward the Elementals are <span style="font-weight: bold">BONUS</span>, not something that will replace them and we’ll get something good in return.  I truly doubt that.
<br />

<br />
Have you ever seen anyone those complaints toward Necro having lots of utility toward the undead?  Well… for my experience, not too many.  I certainly am not complaining.
<br />

<br />
MS IV was nice upgrade, was very impressed with that pet… but how many people have them?  I have only witnessed… only once, someone was using them.  Those who got them, you certainly deserved them.
<br />

<br />
Trading elemental utility for something else, that is already decided to be given to us is not that good of trade.  I dobut the SoE, will ever put any more elemental mobs into the nor design a zone for it.  Nor increase the elemental mobs that we can control in the future game.  Not while some of the mages complaints about the pure <span style="font-weight: bold">BONUS</span> elemental utitlities, like in this board.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Like I have said, Magicians are all about Summoning and Controlling, not just summoning.</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
Archi</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
