Archi,
<br />

<br />
Umm, I think you either didn't read or misread Rytan's LONG message on this board regarding the "summoned" tag and his feelings about our "anti-summoned" abilities/spells.  You keep using the term "elemental".  The devs are not thinking elemental, they are thinking summoned.  There is a difference.  A mob can be elemental but in the zone of its own volition.  Whereas a summoned mob has been brought there against its will.  Rytan made it quite clear that the devs believe the spell line is "anti-summoned" as opposed to "anti-elemental".
<br />

<br />
Using that logic, they have deemed most elemental mobs to NOT be summoned.  In fact the summoned tag on semi-normal mobs in Tak theme LDON fits their logic/lore.
<br />

<br />
If you can convince Rytan and company to see the spell line as an
<br />
anti-elemental line, then the spell series has more value than it does currently.  Otherwise, we can just drop the spell line and use our other nukes.  As for charming, they've pretty much told us that they want to nix mage charms for good.
<br />

<br />
Given the "lemons" Rytan explained in his post, we are trying to make lemonade.  The first step is to not lose a OoW spell or spells to a doomed spell line.  There will be time during the beta (or thru channels like Danille and Xalmat) to hopefully use the spell slot to correct deficiencies in the mage class.
<br />

<br />
I'm not really harping on you Archi, but the terminology used is very important in this case, especially when reading Rytan's lore arguments.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
