			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I would like the focus of the mage to be on nuking and summoned pets, not charmed pets.
<br />

<br />
Charmed pets are a fun distraction for a while, but are not really viable as a long term strategy (we cannot use them solo due to the lack of snare, we cannot use them in raids as they are too unreliable, often we cannot use them in groups because people don't like them).
<br />

<br />
I spent a lot of cash getting hold of Elemental Silence, Call of the Archmage, and Charisma gear (I can boost my Cha to almost 170 unbuffed) and never use them.
<br />

<br />
When first reaching 65, I found that I could charm in BoT and keep up with the pace set by a group with better equipment and many more aas. However, once my gear got a little better, I also found that I do more damage (intelligent damage, in any case), and create less tension, if I forget about charming altogether. 
<br />

<br />
The same goes for mezzing, to a lesser extent. If I attemp to mezz (in BoT or in North Ro), I loose dps. Setting my pets on the adds is far more fun, and allows me to keep nuking at the same time.
<br />

<br />
In my mind, a mage charming and mezzing is similar to a cleric nuking. It's fun for a short while, or might be situationally useful, but is not a long term strategy.
<br />

<br />
So, I would rather we where given better nukes, and better standard pets than upgraded charm and mezz. Don't forget that you can still contnue to charm in BoT after the next expansion, even if we do not get upgraded version of the spells.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
