			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Looking on Lucy, it appears that necros are still getting a new charm at level 70.  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Ah well - Regardless of that,  Mez/Charm are clearly not the main abilities of the mage class - I almost never use them personally.   Are they 'nice to have'?  Sure they are - so were the Velious-era DoTs.
<br />

<br />
The larger issue is this: SOE - Respectfully, Please stop the superficial tinkering of the mage class. Tossing us stripped-down abilities of other classes is horribly un-original, always less powerful than those classes you've copied, and just ticks off some of your customers when you discontinue them with the next expansion.
<br />

<br />
If mages are simply:  Pets, Nukes, Summoned Trinkets, Rods, and CoH - then there are 2 choices:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><span style="text-decoration: underline">1) Significant enhancements along those 5 lines.</span></span>
<br />

<br />
- Pet DPS - crank it up - not to level of GoD charmed mobs, but please much closer than the 20% it is currently.   Its embarasing when your 'DPS specialist class' is always passed over for chanters in Tipt/Vxed.
<br />
- Nuke DPS - crank it up - There should be considerable distance between Druids and Mages (who lack heals, buffs, cures, transports, snares, roots, etc).
<br />
- Summoned Trinkets - Please give us a Summoned Pet Pack (muzzle, girdle, and 2 swords) - and please on a pointer ala Gift of Xev, not in a bag!!!  An upgrade to Muzzle would also be nice.
<br />
- CoH - Group CoH?  Situational I agree, as the anchor would have to stay out of zone -- or perhaps the anchor can equip a summoned item given to him by the calling mage that makes him immune to the Group CoH.  (like the Uqua pieces that negate the zone-wide de-buff).
<br />

<br />
Or
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-style: italic">2) Add a new, *original*, *mage-specific* line.</span></span>
<br />

<br />
- Call of the Spawn?  Integrate a mage spell with spawn cycles to trigger/facilitate in-game events?
<br />
- Fire Pets are Magician Class?  Pets that have Pets - would be nice DPS and original.  Pet's pet would have to obey commands sent to its master by the player (inuding /pet hold) and could possibly scale with focus effects (eg: Minion of Eternity).
<br />
-  Revisit the Anti-summoning Shield?  Single/Group versions?  Add resist checks so its not over-powered?  Or make it a random shot at success like Divine Intervention?
<br />

<br />
These ideas may be great, they may be horrible, they may be impossible to implement regardless of opinion <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> - But please, something original that can be carried forward as a core mage-specific ability for expansions to come.
<br />

<br />
Ah well, that is all.   Thanks for taking the time to read this</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
