				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I never had charm or mez until PoP.  It was fun, I used it soloing/grouping/raiding.  Mez is huge in duels, and usefull in LDoN's as well as charm in LDoN's in Takish.
<br />

<br />
Given the "big picture" though, those spells are NOT usable enough to justify being there.  Mages summon items, drop nukes, and have big burly pets.  That's what we do, let's stick to that.  Of course charm/mez is considered in our "balancing," EVERYTHING IS CONSIDERED IN BALANCING!!!!
<br />

<br />
-Fuck the entire anti summoned line.  It's junk, it's always been junk.
<br />
-Fuck the Velious DOTs we got.  More time spent, not much more efficient.  Total crap.
<br />
-Hello where's my new dispell?!?  Last one was level 52?!?
<br />
-Upgraded Mala?  Hello?  Beuler?
<br />
-Charm and Mez?  Out of character.  I want my PETS to be strong.  That's what I do.  I make pets.  You do too.   Don't design and balance a whole fucking class to be a pet caster with nukes, then give them charm.
